  "text": "For ν > 0 the story is modified in exactly the same way as in the previous subsection. For either sign of z max , the fivebrane now reaches the origin, r = 0, at an angle θ = θ min given in terms of ν by equation [CITATION_1] . As z max → −∞ the solution describes now a fivebrane connected by νN strings to the stack of threebranes. For definiteness, assume the choice of sign for D (i.e., the orientation of the fivebrane) is such that the strings emanate from the D5-brane and terminate on the D3-branes. Upon moving past z max = 0, N strings directed towards the fivebrane are created, and as z max → ∞ (1 − ν)N strings directed away from the threebranes extend between the two types of branes. The case ν = 1/2 is portrayed in Fig. 4 .",
